    <section>
      <h2>How They Actually Differ</h2>

      <h3>Workflow</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Browse specialized remote/hybrid job board, get AI-matched jobs, review tailored resume for each position, approve and apply—all in one platform. Streamlined application process.</p>
      <p><strong>Indeed:</strong> Search jobs using keywords, browse listings, upload resume, apply through Indeed or external company sites. Manual process with no automatic customization.</p>

      <h3>Automation vs Manual Effort</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> AI tailors resumes automatically for each job. You review each one (30-60 seconds) before applying. Job matching happens automatically based on your profile.</p>
      <p><strong>Indeed:</strong> Requires manual job searching, resume uploading, and application customization. No automatic resume tailoring. You must customize applications yourself.</p>

      <h3>Output Quality</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Each resume is tailored to match specific job requirements with ATS optimization. Higher interview rates because applications are precisely targeted.</p>
      <p><strong>Indeed:</strong> Uses your uploaded resume for all applications. No per-job customization unless you manually edit. Quality depends on your resume optimization skills.</p>

      <h3>Learning Curve</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Simple setup—create profile, upload resume, start browsing. The platform guides you through tailoring and applications.</p>
      <p><strong>Indeed:</strong> Straightforward job search interface, but requires learning effective search strategies and resume optimization. Steeper curve for maximizing results.</p>

      <h3>Friction Points</h3>
      <p><strong>Jobsolv:</strong> Requires reviewing each tailored resume (adds 30-60 seconds per application). Smaller job pool focused on remote/hybrid roles.</p>
      <p><strong>Indeed:</strong> Highly competitive—hundreds of applicants per job. No automatic resume tailoring. Requires manual job searching and application customization. Many applications redirect to external company sites.</p>
